This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as segmentation and appearance recovery, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of discriminators and adversarial samples suggests a focus on generative models and deep learning, which are also common in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed dataset and experiments involve image processing and analysis, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the mention of tracking in real-world videos suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
